Healthy eating has a big impact on your overall health.
Eating right can help avoid excess weight gain, improves your mood, combats diseases, improves longevity & boosts your energy. 
Doing right for your body pays off. 
Here are a few tips that you can imply daily to form good long lasting habits.

1Ô∏è‚É£ F·éæ·èü·èå·èö ·éæN ·è¢·é°·éæ·é¢·é¨·èÜN 
Protein are the building blocks of life. 
Every cell in the human body contains protein. 
Protein is very¬†satisfying and keeps us fuller for longer. When we feel more satisfied, we naturally eat less.

2Ô∏è‚É£ ·èö·èî·èÜ·é¢·èü·éª ·é¢·éæ ·èî·é™·é¢·é¨·é°
Staying hydrated is crucial for your health & well being. 
It helps flush out toxins, boosts your immunity, increases brain power, provides energy, boost your metabolism & prevents cramps & sprains. If you find it hard to make the switch try adding lemon and stevia to your water.

3Ô∏è‚É£ ·é¨·é™·é¢ ·èô·é¨·è©·é¨·é¢·é™·è¥·èû·é¨·èö ·èî·èÜ·é¢·éª ·é¨·èô·é¨·é°Y ·é∑·é¨·é™·èû 
Vegetables are important sources of many nutrients. They provide nutrients vital for health & maintenance of your body. 
4Ô∏è‚É£ ·é†·éæN'·é¢ ·èö·é¢·é™·é°·èô·é¨ Y·éæ·èå·é°·èö·é¨·èûF 
Focus on FUELLING your body with nutrients. 
When you starve yourself your body is forced to break down muscle stores in order to create energy. It also changes your metabolism, reduces your bone density & decreases your strength.

5Ô∏è‚É£ ·èü·éæ·éæK ·é∑·éæ·é°·é¨ ·é™·é¢ ·éª·éæ·é∑·é¨
When you cook your own meals at home you have greater control of what goes into your meals. 
6Ô∏è‚É£ ·èû·èÜ·é∑·èÜ·é¢ ·éª·èÜ·è©·éª·èûY ·è¢·é°·éæ·èü·é¨·èö·èö·é¨·é† F·éæ·éæ·é†·èö
Highly processed foods typically come in a box or a bag & contain a number of ingredients. They are high in sugar, fat, salt, & lack fibre, vitamins & minerals. These should be limited as they can have a negative impact on your health.

Bad habits are hard to break, but once you adopt a healthier lifestyle, you WON‚ÄôT REGRET this decision. You won‚Äôt change your mindset and behaviour overnight, so be PATIENT & take it one day at a time.

{NEW} Coconut Creamed Mushrooms + Spinach üå± .
#FaLaLaLa 
I was going to tagline this "not yo grammas creamed spinach" then I thought/remembered...geez...grammas stuff is THE BEST ever...no contest there. This is THAT as far as flavor goes, just most likely a bit healthier because we used our favorite CFC modifications.

Can't wait to hear how you like this one!

makes 4 servings

Ingredients:
1 Tbsp olive oil, or unrefined coconut oil 
1/2 lb. fresh organic baby spinach
1 tsp Dijon mustard
1 cup full fat organic coconut milk, canned 
1 Tbsp gluten free flour, or Arrowroot powder 
1 medium sweet yellow onion, diced
3 cloves fresh garlic, minced
4 cups sliced button mushrooms
2 tsps freshly squeezed lemon juice
sea salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste, about 1/4 teaspoon each 
Instructions:

In a large glass bowl, whisk your coconut milk, Dijon mustard, flour and a pinch of sea salt; whisk until really well combined.

Heat a skillet large with the oil over medium-high heat.

Add in your onions and garlic, saut√© for few minutes until just beginning to soften.

Stir in your mushrooms, and continue cooking for 4-5 minutes more, stirring frequently until golden brown. Season with a tiny pinch of sea salt and pepper.

Squeeze in your fresh lemon juice and stir well.

Reduce the heat to a low, and pour in the coconut milk mixture, then simmer until just thickened, about 4 minutes or so.

Quickly add in the fresh spinach and stir until just wilted, just a minute or two.

Enjoy warm!üíö
